modules.description: Provides functions to stream data in and out of tar archives, including reading headers, extracting files, and writing entries. Works with byte sequences, file paths, and tar header structures. Used to process large archives incrementally without loading entire files into memory.

Provides functions to extract, create, and process Tar files using Eio, including extracting entries to a directory, creating archives from a directory, and folding over tar contents. Operates on Tar.Header.t, Eio.Path.t, and Eio.Flow.sink types, with support for filtering entries during extraction or creation. Enables writing individual files, headers, and extended headers to a tar stream, and handles errors during decoding or file operations.
